The paper deals with shape analysis and deformation of surfaces, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of optimization algorithms and statistical analysis also suggests a connection to computational geometry (cs.CG) and machine learning (cs.MM) subfields. Finally, the application of the proposed algorithms to human body shapes and brain structures indicates a potential overlap with the field of medical imaging (cs.LG).
